c:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 mb-6 not-prose","children":["$","ul",null,{"className":"space-y-2.5 border-l-4 border-yellow-400/50 pl-4","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"Four-marker test detects 90%+ of early-stage pancreatic cancers"}]]}],["$","li","1",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"Research-stage only—no clinical use yet, no regulatory approval"}]]}],["$","li","2",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"Early detection matters, but survival gains still unproven"}]]}]]}]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 article-prose max-w-none","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":["Pancreatic cancer remains one of the deadliest malignancies not because it’s untreatable, but because it’s almost always detected too late. A ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2024/05/240515123417.htm","children":"new blood test"}]," targeting two previously unknown proteins—combined with two established biomarkers—now offers a glimmer of progress: in lab validation, it identified over 90% of early-stage cases, where survival rates climb dramatically."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["The study, published in ",["$","em",null,{"children":"Clinical Cancer Research"}],", represents a methodological leap. Researchers analyzed blood samples from 300+ patients (a mix of diagnosed cases and controls) and found the four-marker panel outperformed current tools like CA19-9, particularly in Stage I/II disease. That’s critical, since ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://seer.cancer.gov/statfacts/html/pancreas.html","children":"only 12% of pancreatic cancers"}]," are caught early enough for surgery—the sole curative option."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Yet the headline numbers obscure important context. This was a retrospective analysis, not a prospective trial. The samples came from a single institution, and while the accuracy is striking, real-world performance in asymptomatic populations—where false positives could trigger unnecessary procedures—remains untested."}],"\n",["$","div",null,{"className":"not-prose my-8 pt-6 border-t border-white/10","children":[null,["$","div",null,{"className":"glass-card overflow-hidden mb-4 !hover:transform-none","children":["$","img",null,{"src":"/images/articles/pancreatic-cancer-blood-test-real-progress-with-re/subtitle.jpg","alt":"A study with rare promise—and the usual caveats","className":"w-full h-auto max-h-[400px] object-cover"}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-text-secondary italic text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium","children":"A study with rare promise—and the usual caveats"}]]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["For patients today, nothing changes. The test isn’t FDA-approved, nor is it available outside research settings. Even if validated, its role would likely be secondary: a tool for high-risk groups (e.g., those with genetic syndromes or chronic pancreatitis), not population-wide screening. ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.mdanderson.org/research/departments-labs-institutes/labs/maitra-lab.html","children":"Dr. Anirban Maitra"}],", a pancreatic cancer specialist unaffiliated with the study, notes that ‘early detection is only half the battle—we still lack therapies that exploit this window effectively.’"]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["The study’s limitations are instructive. The sample size, while robust for biomarker research, wasn’t stratified by demographics or comorbidities. And as with all blood-based tests, the risk of overdiagnosis—detecting indolent lesions that might never progress—looms. The ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.genomicsengland.co.uk/","children":"UK’s 100,000 Genomes Project"}]," has shown how even high-accuracy tests can falter in diverse populations without rigorous validation."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["What’s undeniable is the urgency. Pancreatic cancer’s five-year survival rate hovers at ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.cancer.net/cancer-types/pancreatic-cancer/statistics","children":"12%"}],", largely unchanged for decades. A test that reliably flags early disease could, ","$L15",", shift that needle—but only if paired with better treatments and clearer guidelines on who to test."]}],"\n","$L16"]}]
